This is voter disenfranchisement, period. It's wrong AND it also hurts our chances of winning. South Carolinians and anyone who believes in democracy should be outraged.

This election will come down to a handful of votes, and we need the resources to make sure every 👏 vote 👏 is 👏 counted 👏.

Chip in today to make sure we're prepared. Link in bio!

Thirty-eight states have expanded Medicaid. If my neighbors lived in any one of them, hundreds of thousands could receive quality, affordable health insurance.

It is shameful, and Lindsey Graham called it "courageous" to turn down this funding.

This was just one way that the Senator demonstrated that he is no longer worthy of that title at tonight's debate.

node.text:
When we were thinking about how we wanted to launch @TheDemocrats’ new podcast, we thought long and hard about the biggest issues facing our country today—and one of the most important ones is voting rights. We decided to approach it through the lens of talking to leaders on the front lines of this fight in the state where voting rights are under attack like never before: Texas.

I’m so excited to host former Secretary @JulianCastroTX and the @TexasDemocrats’ Voter Protection Director, Rose Clouston, on our second-ever episode of “Welcome to the Party.” Click the link in my bio to listen.
